        {
          "$type": "text",
          "text": "James, thanks for telling me. That took something.\n\nDon't carry guilt about this. You told me now, and that's what matters.\n\nHere's where I have to be straight with you: diagnosing what's happening with your foot and prescribing treatment is outside what I can do. I'm your running coach, not a medical professional. What you're describing, pain bad enough to stop you mid-run, and a pattern that's gotten worse over time, needs a physiotherapist or sports medicine doctor to assess. Not a guess from me.\n\nThat's the clear next step. Go back to your physio before you run again. Tell them exactly what you told me: you ran through the pain, it's gotten worse, you had to stop three times. They need the full picture to give you an accurate assessment.\n\nWhat I can do is this. Once you have clearance and guidance from your physio, I'll rebuild your return plan around whatever constraints they give you. Your Daniels-Gilbert zones are based on a 44:00 10K, so the fitness foundation is there. It doesn't disappear. A setback like this is a detour, not an erasure.\n\nOne practical thing worth knowing: your physiotherapist's clearance language will shape what I build. \"Easy running okay\" means one thing. \"Walk-run intervals only\" means another. The more specific their guidance, the better I can tailor the plan.\n\nIs there anything getting in the way of seeing your physio this week?"
        }
      ],
      "messageId": "msg_01BiG9fSDKxN2EwFBEbTiKas"
    }
